reviewText: A delightful fun filled movie about two boys and their misadventures trying to keep a seal.  The movie has plenty of water mishaps.  It provides plenty of great light-hearted  entertainment.  Great to finally have it on DVD.
summary: A funny story about 2 boys and their attempt to keep a seal.

reviewText: Saw Sammy the Way-Out Seal as a child and loved it.Now I watch it as an adult and still love it.Robert Culp &  Bill Mumy are great and a very young Ann Jillian as Porsche 'Rocky' Sylvester adds to the fun.The pool party is the highlight of the film.A great early 1960's Disney comedy.

reviewText: A determinately cute movie about two boys and their pet seal.  It's positively zealous in its attempt to be fun and playful, loaded with plenty of laughs and a lot of antics that anyone would enjoy watching.  Initially, it was shown as a two part episode on TV.  You can see exactly where they cut for commercials, no one bothered to smooth out the abrupt edits.  The film transfer is middling at best.  It doesn't feel like they were trying to preserve anything precious, which is a shame, because this is a good movie.
summary: "Sea lions have to stay wet ya dope!"

reviewText: If you are a Disney fan you no doubt have seen this wonderful story.  Easily one of my older Disney classics.  The seal definitely steals the show and you'll find yourself laughing out loud many times with his antics.  Well played by the actors as well and you'll recognize many of them.  I highly recommend this movie which is fun for young and old alike.  They don't make movies like this any more.
